<dl id="n11129c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11129c">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11129c"> 129(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Chat-Lucile / Renan Henriette</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il n&apos;y a aucune difficulte&eacute; &agrave; retrouver Chateaubriand dans Rene&eacute; et dans Ame&eacute;lie sa soeur Lucile, qui fut la confidente de&eacute;vou&eacute;e de son adolescence et qui devait arriver biento&ocirc;t (1804) au terme d&apos;une destin&eacute;e f&eacute;conde en vicissitudes, finalement troubl&eacute;e par la folie, une folie douce et tre&egrave;s touchante. <br><font color="green">[It is not difficult to recognize Chateaubriand in R&eacute;n&eacute; and his sister Lucile in Am&eacute;lie who was the most devoted confidante of his youth and was soon (in 1804) to end a life abounding in vicissitudes, finally spoilt by madness, a mild, most touching madness.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, <i>Ren&eacute;</i> [<b>Notice Historique et Analytique</b>] 83</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Henriette is Renan&apos;s sister. Lucile was Chata </mm> </dd></dl>
